2652bool CXXConstructorDecl::isDefaultConstructor() const {
2653 // C++ [class.default.ctor]p1:
2654 // A default constructor for a class X is a constructor of class X for
2655 // which each parameter that is not a function parameter pack has a default
2656 // argument (including the case of a constructor with no parameters)
2657 return getMinRequiredArguments() == 0;
2658}
2659
2660bool
2661CXXConstructorDecl::isCopyConstructor(unsigned &TypeQuals) const {
2662 return isCopyOrMoveConstructor(TypeQuals) &&
2663 getParamDecl(0)->getType()->isLValueReferenceType();
2664}
2665
2666bool CXXConstructorDecl::isMoveConstructor(unsigned &TypeQuals) const {
2667 return isCopyOrMoveConstructor(TypeQuals) &&
2668 getParamDecl(0)->getType()->isRValueReferenceType();
2669}
2670
2671/// Determine whether this is a copy or move constructor.
2672bool CXXConstructorDecl::isCopyOrMoveConstructor(unsigned &TypeQuals) const {
2673 // C++ [class.copy]p2:
2674 // A non-template constructor for class X is a copy constructor
2675 // if its first parameter is of type X&, const X&, volatile X& or
2676 // const volatile X&, and either there are no other parameters
2677 // or else all other parameters have default arguments (8.3.6).
2678 // C++0x [class.copy]p3:
2679 // A non-template constructor for class X is a move constructor if its
2680 // first parameter is of type X&&, const X&&, volatile X&&, or
2681 // const volatile X&&, and either there are no other parameters or else
2682 // all other parameters have default arguments.
2683 if (!hasOneParamOrDefaultArgs() || getPrimaryTemplate() != nullptr ||
2684 getDescribedFunctionTemplate() != nullptr)
2685 return false;
2686
2687 const ParmVarDecl *Param = getParamDecl(0);
2688
2689 // Do we have a reference type?
2690 const auto *ParamRefType = Param->getType()->getAs<ReferenceType>();
2691 if (!ParamRefType)
2692 return false;
2693
2694 // Is it a reference to our class type?
2695 ASTContext &Context = getASTContext();
2696
2697 CanQualType PointeeType
2698 = Context.getCanonicalType(ParamRefType->getPointeeType());
2699 CanQualType ClassTy
2700 = Context.getCanonicalType(Context.getTagDeclType(getParent()));
2701 if (PointeeType.getUnqualifiedType() != ClassTy)
2702 return false;
2703
2704 // FIXME: other qualifiers?
2705
2706 // We have a copy or move constructor.
2707 TypeQuals = PointeeType.getCVRQualifiers();
2708 return true;
2709}
2710
2711bool CXXConstructorDecl::isConvertingConstructor(bool AllowExplicit) const {
2712 // C++ [class.conv.ctor]p1:
2713 // A constructor declared without the function-specifier explicit
2714 // that can be called with a single parameter specifies a
2715 // conversion from the type of its first parameter to the type of
2716 // its class. Such a constructor is called a converting
2717 // constructor.
2718 if (isExplicit() && !AllowExplicit)
2719 return false;
2720
2721 // FIXME: This has nothing to do with the definition of converting
2722 // constructor, but is convenient for how we use this function in overload
2723 // resolution.
2724 return getNumParams() == 0
2725 ? getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>()->isVariadic()
2726 : getMinRequiredArguments() <= 1;
2727}
2728
2729bool CXXConstructorDecl::isSpecializationCopyingObject() const {
2730 if (!hasOneParamOrDefaultArgs() || getDescribedFunctionTemplate() != nullptr)
2731 return false;
2732
2733 const ParmVarDecl *Param = getParamDecl(0);
2734
2735 ASTContext &Context = getASTContext();
2736 CanQualType ParamType = Context.getCanonicalType(Param->getType());
2737
2738 // Is it the same as our class type?
2739 CanQualType ClassTy
2740 = Context.getCanonicalType(Context.getTagDeclType(getParent()));
2741 if (ParamType.getUnqualifiedType() != ClassTy)
2742 return false;
2743
2744 return true;
2745}

2954/// Retrieve the storage duration for the materialized temporary.
2955StorageDuration LifetimeExtendedTemporaryDecl::getStorageDuration() const {
2956 const ValueDecl *ExtendingDecl = getExtendingDecl();
2957 if (!ExtendingDecl)
2958 return SD_FullExpression;
2959 // FIXME: This is not necessarily correct for a temporary materialized
2960 // within a default initializer.
2961 if (isa<FieldDecl>(ExtendingDecl))
2962 return SD_Automatic;
2963 // FIXME: This only works because storage class specifiers are not allowed
2964 // on decomposition declarations.
2965 if (isa<BindingDecl>(ExtendingDecl))
2966 return ExtendingDecl->getDeclContext()->isFunctionOrMethod() ? SD_Automatic
2967 : SD_Static;
2968 return cast<VarDecl>(ExtendingDecl)->getStorageDuration();
2969}
2970
2971APValue *LifetimeExtendedTemporaryDecl::getOrCreateValue(bool MayCreate) const {
2972 assert(getStorageDuration() == SD_Static &&
2973 "don't need to cache the computed value for this temporary");
2974 if (MayCreate && !Value) {
2975 Value = (new (getASTContext()) APValue);
2976 getASTContext().addDestruction(Value);
2977 }
2978 assert(Value && "may not be null");
2979 return Value;
2980}

3031
3032void UsingDecl::addShadowDecl(UsingShadowDecl *S) {
3033 assert(std::find(shadow_begin(), shadow_end(), S) == shadow_end() &&
3034 "declaration already in set");
3035 assert(S->getUsingDecl() == this);
3036
3037 if (FirstUsingShadow.getPointer())
3038 S->UsingOrNextShadow = FirstUsingShadow.getPointer();
3039 FirstUsingShadow.setPointer(S);
3040}
3041
3042void UsingDecl::removeShadowDecl(UsingShadowDecl *S) {
3043 assert(std::find(shadow_begin(), shadow_end(), S) != shadow_end() &&
3044 "declaration not in set");
3045 assert(S->getUsingDecl() == this);
3046
3047 // Remove S from the shadow decl chain. This is O(n) but hopefully rare.
3048
3049 if (FirstUsingShadow.getPointer() == S) {
3050 FirstUsingShadow.setPointer(
3051 dyn_cast<UsingShadowDecl>(S->UsingOrNextShadow));
3052 S->UsingOrNextShadow = this;
3053 return;
3054 }
3055
3056 UsingShadowDecl *Prev = FirstUsingShadow.getPointer();
3057 while (Prev->UsingOrNextShadow != S)
3058 Prev = cast<UsingShadowDecl>(Prev->UsingOrNextShadow);
3059 Prev->UsingOrNextShadow = S->UsingOrNextShadow;
3060 S->UsingOrNextShadow = this;
3061}

3187VarDecl *BindingDecl::getHoldingVar() const {
3188 Expr *B = getBinding();
3189 if (!B)
3190 return nullptr;

3285/// Determine if T is a valid 'struct _GUID' of the shape that we expect.
3286static bool isValidStructGUID(ASTContext &Ctx, QualType T) {
3287 // FIXME: We only need to check this once, not once each time we compute a
3288 // GUID APValue.
3289 using MatcherRef = llvm::function_ref<bool(QualType)>;
3290
3291 auto IsInt = [&Ctx](unsigned N) {
3292 return [&Ctx, N](QualType T) {
3293 return T->isUnsignedIntegerOrEnumerationType() &&
3294 Ctx.getIntWidth(T) == N;
3295 };
3296 };
3297
3298 auto IsArray = [&Ctx](MatcherRef Elem, unsigned N) {
3299 return [&Ctx, Elem, N](QualType T) {
3300 const ConstantArrayType *CAT = Ctx.getAsConstantArrayType(T);
3301 return CAT && CAT->getSize() == N && Elem(CAT->getElementType());
3302 };
3303 };
3304
3305 auto IsStruct = [](std::initializer_list<MatcherRef> Fields) {
3306 return [Fields](QualType T) {
3307 const RecordDecl *RD = T->getAsRecordDecl();
3308 if (!RD || RD->isUnion())
3309 return false;
3310 RD = RD->getDefinition();
3311 if (!RD)
3312 return false;
3313 if (auto *CXXRD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD))
3314 if (CXXRD->getNumBases())
3315 return false;
3316 auto MatcherIt = Fields.begin();
3317 for (const FieldDecl *FD : RD->fields()) {
3318 if (FD->isUnnamedBitfield()) continue;
3319 if (FD->isBitField() || MatcherIt == Fields.end() ||
3320 !(*MatcherIt)(FD->getType()))
3321 return false;
3322 ++MatcherIt;
3323 }
3324 return MatcherIt == Fields.end();
3325 };
3326 };
3327
3328 // We expect an {i32, i16, i16, [8 x i8]}.
3329 return IsStruct({IsInt(32), IsInt(16), IsInt(16), IsArray(IsInt(8), 8)})(T);
3330}
3331
3332APValue &MSGuidDecl::getAsAPValue() const {
3333 if (APVal.isAbsent() && isValidStructGUID(getASTContext(), getType())) {
3334 using llvm::APInt;
3335 using llvm::APSInt;
3336 APVal = APValue(APValue::UninitStruct(), 0, 4);
3337 APVal.getStructField(0) = APValue(APSInt(APInt(32, PartVal.Part1), true));
3338 APVal.getStructField(1) = APValue(APSInt(APInt(16, PartVal.Part2), true));
3339 APVal.getStructField(2) = APValue(APSInt(APInt(16, PartVal.Part3), true));
3340 APValue &Arr = APVal.getStructField(3) =
3341 APValue(APValue::UninitArray(), 8, 8);
3342 for (unsigned I = 0; I != 8; ++I) {
3343 Arr.getArrayInitializedElt(I) =
3344 APValue(APSInt(APInt(8, PartVal.Part4And5[I]), true));
3345 }
3346 // Register this APValue to be destroyed if necessary. (Note that the
3347 // MSGuidDecl destructor is never run.)
3348 getASTContext().addDestruction(&APVal);
3349 }
3350
3351 return APVal;
3352}

3354static const char *getAccessName(AccessSpecifier AS) {
3355 switch (AS) {
3356 case AS_none:
3357 llvm_unreachable("Invalid access specifier!");
3358 case AS_public:
3359 return "public";
3360 case AS_private:
3361 return "private";
3362 case AS_protected:
3363 return "protected";
3364 }
3365 llvm_unreachable("Invalid access specifier!");
3366}

3368const StreamingDiagnostic &clang::operator<<(const StreamingDiagnostic &DB,
3369 AccessSpecifier AS) {
3370 return DB << getAccessName(AS);
3371}
